creator: Mighty Networks
descriptionHtml:
Educators generate curiosity. Curiosity sparks ideas. Ideas transform the status quo. Join a purposeful community of educators championing ideas and pushing the status quo.
TED-Ed’s Educator Hub is a vibrant, collaborative community that brings together educators participating in TED-Ed programs around the world to learn about idea development and presentation literacy so that we can amplify students’ and teachers’ ideas and transform education.
Everyday, millions of people turn to TED for innovative ideas. TED helps speakers deliver their best ideas in an effective and engaging way and then amplify those ideas. TED-Ed adapts TED’s ability to help speakers into programs created specifically for educators and students. We’ve helped thousands of educators and students come together to connect on ideas worth spreading. We stand with and for educators and students, because we believe that if every educator and student shares their best idea, we can transform learning environments around the world and develop a vibrant global educational community.

In this space members will:
Learn from and support educators across TED-Ed programs who are motivated to amplify ideas.
Engage in transformative discussions that matter.
Find educators near you, in similar roles, and who are interested in the same causes or ideas as you.
Sign up for workshops with the TED team, calls with other educators and other virtual TED events all in one place.
Improve skills and add and access free valuable resources.
Do it all on the go with both the app and web version.
